1
00:00:05,300 --> 00:00:11,400
The progressive position
is the intermediate position;

2
00:00:11,400 --> 00:00:16,700
progressive devotion is enacted
from the intermediate plane,

3
00:00:16,700 --> 00:00:18,800
vision of madhyama-adhikārī.

4
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:22,100
[Guru: Heavier than the Himalayas]

5
00:00:22,100 --> 00:00:27,400
Guru Mahārāj also pointed out,
in Gauḍīya Maṭh, he said,

6
00:00:27,400 --> 00:00:35,740
“Controversy was kept
from the neophyte section

7
00:00:36,440 --> 00:00:43,260
because they will be unable
to handle that—laghu.

8
00:00:43,260 --> 00:00:47,250
Guru means ‘heavy’,
heavier than the Himalayas.

9
00:00:47,300 --> 00:00:50,800
Laghu means ‘light’,
light as a feather.

10
00:00:50,800 --> 00:00:56,700
So we see what is the cliche,
stereotype—light as a feather.

11
00:00:56,700 --> 00:00:58,700
A breeze comes in, 
lifts the feather up,

12
00:00:58,700 --> 00:01:01,700
it’s twirled around 
and then falls in there.

13
00:01:01,700 --> 00:01:07,180
Another breeze comes, lifts the feather up, 
drops it in another place.

14
00:01:07,600 --> 00:01:11,820
The plight of the neophyte—
hearing one thing:

15
00:01:11,820 --> 00:01:13,800
“That makes sense!”,
and going in the …

16
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:16,120
hearing in another place the opposite— 
going in another place:

17
00:01:16,120 --> 00:01:17,700
“That makes sense!”,
going that plane …

18
00:01:17,700 --> 00:01:21,100
Confusion. 
Unable to discriminate

19
00:01:21,100 --> 00:01:24,600
between higher, lower,
desirable, undesirable,

20
00:01:24,600 --> 00:01:29,900
genuine devotion, feigned devotion, 
counterfeit devotion;

21
00:01:29,900 --> 00:01:34,930
what is condemned
cannot understand

22
00:01:34,930 --> 00:01:37,000
what is in their own interest.

23
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:42,200
So laghu has to connect to guru.

24
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:44,850
Why guru is heavier
than Himalaya?

25
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:50,850
tasmād guruṁ prapadyeta
jijñāsuḥ śreya uttamam
 

26
00:01:50,850 --> 00:01:56,200
śābde pare ca niṣṇātaṁ
brahmaṇy upaśamāśrayam
[SB: 11.3.21]

27
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:59,900
When we are indicated
to go to guru.

28
00:01:59,900 --> 00:02:02,610
What is guru—
brāhmaṇa;

29
00:02:02,610 --> 00:02:06,300
totally, so much sheltered 
in the spiritual conception,

30
00:02:06,300 --> 00:02:12,800
cannot be moved by any misconception,
that personality.

31
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:17,510
Sometimes Guru Mahārāj would say
this śikhā, will be …

32
00:02:17,510 --> 00:02:21,120
he says,
“Take the śikhā and tie—

33
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:26,000
the laghu disciples shall tie their śikhā
to the lotus feet of guru.

34
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:31,120
So when the winds of misconception come,
being tossed this way and that way,

35
00:02:31,120 --> 00:02:33,580
still being tied 
to the lotus feet of Gurudev,

36
00:02:33,580 --> 00:02:39,670
will survive the onslaught 
of misconception.

37
00:02:40,200 --> 00:02:46,100
So ... and, just to continue
the conceit, that

38
00:02:46,100 --> 00:02:51,200
guru kāraṇa ... dhāraṇam—

39
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:57,010
the captain of the boat—
human form of life being the boat,

40
00:02:57,500 --> 00:03:07,680
the guru being the captain 
and the winds are vedā, Kṛṣṇa coming …
 

41
00:03:07,680 --> 00:03:17,830
how to negotiate those winds,
is how to sail the boat properly.

42
00:03:17,830 --> 00:03:20,020
What was it that I saw
the other day,

43
00:03:20,020 --> 00:03:25,640
when you go into the wind?

44
00:03:25,640 --> 00:03:29,500
What is it called? 
It’s a nautical term.

45
00:03:29,500 --> 00:03:33,310
Where they decide at some
point to turn the boat and ...

46
00:03:33,310 --> 00:03:38,100
Tack! 
So it is called ‘tack’.

47
00:03:38,100 --> 00:03:42,100
So sometimes what
appears to be counterintuitive,

48
00:03:42,100 --> 00:03:48,100
guru will know that
what is favorable, what is unfavorable.

49
00:03:48,100 --> 00:03:50,300
Laghu needs to be 
in connection with guru,

50
00:03:50,300 --> 00:03:53,300
the disciple needs to be 
in connection with guru

51
00:03:53,300 --> 00:03:56,700
to properly navigate,
to understand

52
00:03:56,700 --> 00:04:00,380
what is the purport
of the scriptures.

